<h2>Parabola Calculator version 2.0</h2>
<div class=3D"imgdiv">
  <!-- header image at top of pg -->=20
  <img alt=3D"Small Version of Main Program Window" src=3D"https://mscir.tr=
ipod.com/parabola/images/0.gif" height=3D"200" width=3D"398">
</div>
<div class=3D"contentdiv">
  <h4>About This Program</h4>
  This Freeware program was written to help you design solar collector or w=
ifi projects using parabolic reflectors.=20
  Whether you're improving the signal strength of your wifi antenna, or des=
igning a satellite antenna or solar trough,=20
  this program calculates the focal length and (x, y) coordinates for a par=
abola of any diameter and depth. It can=20
  help you determine what size and shape to make your parabola very quickly=
. Version 2 includes Wifi calculations
  for centered or offset feedhorn dishes. If you would like modifications t=
o the program to make it more useful to=20
  you or to send feedback, you can email me <a href=3D"mailto:mscir@yahoo.c=
om">here</a>. =20
 =20
  <h4>Credits</h4>
  Thanks to <b>Frank Schindler</b> for the curve fitting code used by this =
program, you can see his page <a href=3D"http://www.codeguru.com/vb/gen/vb_=
misc/article.php/c2729/" target=3D"_blank">here</a>.=20
  <p>Thanks to <b>Bernhard S. M=FCller</b> for helping develop and beta tes=
ting version 1, you can see his site <a href=3D"http://www.mueller-solartec=
hnik.com/" target=3D"_blank">here</a>.
  </p><p>Thanks to <b>Edisher Giorgadze</b> for helping develop and beta te=
sting version 2, you can see his page <a href=3D"http://www.amsatnet.com/p5=
.html" target=3D"_blank">here</a>.
  </p><p>Thanks to <b>Paul Wade</b> for supplying the WiFi text, calculatio=
ns and code, they were copied directly from his hdl_ant program, you can vi=
sit his site and download his program <a href=3D"http://www.qsl.net/n1bwt/"=
 target=3D"_blank">here</a>.
 =20
  </p><h4>Download the Program</h4>
  <p>This program was written in Visual Basic 6, and should run on Window 9=
5 or later. The program will run under Linux
  using Wine if you copy the dependancy files into the folder where the pro=
gram resides. The program requires Visual=20
  Basic 6 runtime files, your computer may already have them installed. I w=
ould try downloading the smaller file (program
  only) first and seeing if it runs. If not, delete it and download the Win=
dows Installer to perform a standard Windows=20
  installation.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href=3D"https://mscir.tripod.com/parabola/parabola2.zip">Downloa=
d Parabola.exe (137 kB)</a> (program only, does not include Visual Basic ru=
ntime files)</li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://mscir.tripod.com/parabola/parabola2_installer.zi=
p">Download Windows Installer (1.65 MB)</a> (run Setup.exe to perform stand=
ard Windows installation)</li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://mscir.tripod.com/parabola/parabola2_vb6_sourceco=
de.zip">Download VB6 Source Code (155 kB)</a></li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://mscir.tripod.com/parabola/parabola2_linuxfiles.z=
ip">Download VB6 runtime files for Linux Wine (740 kB)</a></li>
  </ul>
